710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rat problems\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 411}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 440}, {\"ngram\": \"overflowing waste bins\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source: AP / Francois Mori / David Goldman With the Paris Olympics opening night just a few days away, the final preparations are under way.\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999912142812, \"rank\": 7.580129074511404e-09, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\", \"score\": 0.9999998485423135, \"rank\": 1.5145789852155157e-07, \"text\": \"David Goldman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_P._Goldman\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"opening night\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the final preparations\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the city authorities that also includes making sure that all the rats 'stay in the sewers'.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city authorities\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"all the rats\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris vermin, a feature in French literature from \\\"Les Miserables\\\" to \\\"the Phantom of the Opera\\\", are frequently drawn into a contemporary debate about cleanliness in the French capital - and could be an embarrassment as the Olympics spotlight falls on Paris.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_literature\", \"score\": 0.999998857111421, \"rank\": 1.1428897943086335e-06, \"text\": \"French literature\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_literature\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_literature\"}, {\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.6573063714983631, \"rank\": 0.5212284311361494, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a feature\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Les Miserables\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"the Phantom\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opera\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"a contemporary debate\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"cleanliness\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"an embarrassment\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics spotlight\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All of the Olympic sites and celebration areas were analysed (for rats) before the Games,\\\" deputy mayor Anne-Claire Boux, who has responsibility for public health, told AFP in an interview.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.999999984182523, \"rank\": 1.581689975002693e-08, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic sites\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration areas\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"rats\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"deputy mayor Anne-Claire Boux\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"responsibility\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"public health\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"an interview\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1163}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as ordering a deep clean to remove any food residues that might tempt the scurriers from their underground lairs, the mayor's rodent specialists also worked to close up exit points from the sewers around the sites.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a deep clean\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"any food residues\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"the scurriers\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"their underground lairs\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"the mayor's rodent specialists\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"exit points\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"the sites\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Where there were areas with lots of rats we put traps in place ahead of the Games,\\\" Boux continued, adding that both mechanical rat-traps and chemical solutions were used to reduce troublesome populations.\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1596, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"areas\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"rats\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"traps\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"Boux\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"both mechanical rat-traps and chemical solutions\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"troublesome populations\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The park behind the Eiffel Tower, where the beach volleyball is set to take place, and the Louvre gardens, where the Olympic cauldron is set to burn, are popular picnic spots - and previously rat infested.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The park\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach volleyball\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"the Louvre gardens\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic cauldron\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"popular picnic spots\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"previously rat\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ultimately, no-one should aim to exterminate Paris' rats, and they are useful in maintaining the sewers,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no-one\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The point is that they should stay in the sewers.\\\"\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The point\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewers\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A viral social media campaign in 2021 called #SaccageParis (#TrashedParis) led to residents posting pictures of overflowing bins, badly maintained street furniture or overgrown green spaces that hurt the city's cultivated reputation for elegance.\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A viral social media campaign\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"#SaccageParis\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2034}, {\"ngram\": \"TrashedParis\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2049}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"pictures\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"overflowing bins\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"street furniture\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"overgrown green spaces\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's cultivated reputation\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"elegance\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city unveiled a \\\"manifesto for beauty\\\" afterwards in response to the criticism.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2307, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"manifesto\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2254}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"the criticism\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the Olympics, its boulevards and squares have been thoroughly spruced up, with many historic buildings given a makeover.\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"its boulevards\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"squares\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2358}, {\"ngram\": \"many historic buildings\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2420}, {\"ngram\": \"a makeover\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boux stressed that rat problems were first and foremost caused by food being left out on the ground, or from overflowing waste bins, many of which are being changed around Paris ton ew rat-proof versions.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2612, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boux\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"rat problems\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2539}, {\"ngram\": \"overflowing waste bins\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The most important thing is that the bins are sealed and closed,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most important thing\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"the bins\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city's rodent exterminators - known as the \\\"Smash\\\" team - have also had an advisory role to the Paris organising committee, suggesting ways to design their sites to keep them clean and orderly.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2824, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city's rodent exterminators\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2755}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Smash\\\" team\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"an advisory role\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"their sites\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 2889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Responsibility for waste removal and street-cleaning will fall to the city's 7,500-strong cleaning and collection teams, whose three-week strike last year led to an estimated 10,000 tonnes of garbage pile up in the streets.\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Responsibility\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"waste removal\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"street-cleaning\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's 7,500-strong cleaning and collection teams\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3042}, {\"ngram\": \"whose three-week strike\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3067}, {\"ngram\": \"an estimated 10,000 tonnes\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3111}, {\"ngram\": \"garbage pile\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3127}, {\"ngram\": \"the streets\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are set to earn bonuses of up to 1,900 euros ($3,119) for working through the Olympic period, while private contractors are also set to reinforce efforts to keep the city clean.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bonuses\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 1,900 euros\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3197}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic period\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3245}, {\"ngram\": \"private contractors\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"efforts\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3306}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not at all worried (about rats),\\\" deputy mayor in charge of waste, Antoine Guillou, told AFP.\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.999999984182523, \"rank\": 1.581689975002693e-08, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rats\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" deputy mayor\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3384}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3394}, {\"ngram\": \"waste\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3403}, {\"ngram\": \"Antoine Guillou\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On the contrary, the Games will help us show definitively that this idea that you run into lots of rats in Paris is false.\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3541, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.800917744158768e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3449}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3460}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3473}, {\"ngram\": \"this idea\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3506}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"rats\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are some, we deal with them, but they are not an issue specific to Paris nor on the scale that is sometimes suggested in a caricatural way,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3637, \"